# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Rust build artifacts
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/target
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb

# Cargo.lock IS committed — this workspace produces binaries (fpa-gateway, fpa-cli),
# so the lockfile is intentionally tracked for reproducible builds. Do not ignore it.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Machine-local / secret files (these MUST NOT travel between machines)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Note: .claude/settings.local.json (per-host permission grants) is ignored at the
# very bottom of this file — it must come after the .claude/** re-include to win.
# Local environment / secrets.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# OS / editor cruft
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Portable project state — INTENTIONALLY TRACKED so it follows you across machines.
# The `!` rules below defend this state against any broad ignore pattern that may
# be added later. Do not add a bare `.kbd-orchestrator/`, `.codex/`, etc. above.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# KBD orchestrator state (project.json, constraints.md, phase/waypoint state).
!.kbd-orchestrator/
!.kbd-orchestrator/**

# OpenSpec specs, changes, and archive — the spec source of truth.
!openspec/
!openspec/**

# OpenSpec / agent tool skills + slash commands (codex, claude, kimi, opencode).
# Shared, version-controlled team config — keep them tracked.
!.codex/
!.codex/**
!.kimi/
!.kimi/**
!.opencode/
!.opencode/**
# Track committed Claude config (commands, skills)...
!.claude/
!.claude/**
# ...but the machine-local override must stay ignored. This negation comes AFTER
# the re-include above because git applies the last matching pattern — a `!` rule
# placed earlier would be overridden by `!.claude/**`.
.claude/settings.local.json
